def get_qspoint(signal,r_point):
    r_point_y=signal[r_point]
    r_point_x=r_point
    # next we find the slope made by the line connecting to the s point
    for j in range(r_point_x,r_point_x+150):
        if signal[j]<signal[j+1] and signal[j]<1.5:
            break
    for k in range(r_point_x,r_point_x-50,-1):
        if x[k-1]>x[k] and signal[k]<1.5:
            break
    q_point_y=signal[k]
    q_point_x=k
    s_point_y=signal[j]
    s_point_x=j
    return(q_point_x,s_point_x)

def get_st_segment(signal,r_point):
    s_point=r_point+15
    t_point=r_point+45
    return(s_point,t_point)

code to take input signal and give analysis of heart rate¶

In [15]:
def analyze_mean_hr(signal,fs=250):
    '''
    signal : 1d numpy array
    fs : rate of sampling
    '''
    xqrs1 = processing.XQRS(sig=signal, fs=fs)
    xqrs1.detect()
    wfdb.plot_items(signal=signal, ann_samp=[xqrs1.qrs_inds])
    mean_hr=processing.hr.calc_mean_hr(processing.hr.calc_rr(xqrs1.qrs_inds,fs),fs)
    instantaneous_hr=processing.hr.compute_hr(len(signal),xqrs1.qrs_inds,fs)
    if mean_hr>=60 and mean_hr<=90:
        return(mean_hr," Normal heart rate")
    elif mean_hr>=50 and mean_hr<=100:
        return(mean_hr," Border range heart rate")
    elif mean_hr<50 and mean_hr>0:
        return(mean_hr," bradicardia")
    elif mean_hr>100:
        return(mean_hr," trachycardia")
    else:
        return("You should not be alive or check the equipment!!!")
